$ .NET attributes for caller information

Classes that inherit from `→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Attribute` that provide information about a caller are:
 • `→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Runtime/CompilerServices/CallerArgumentExpressionAttribute`
 • `→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Runtime/CompilerServices/CallerFilePathAttribute`
 • `→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Runtime/CompilerServices/CallerLineNumberAttribute`
 • `→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Runtime/CompilerServices/CallerMemberNameAttribute`

{ Example

  { Class for logging

    gh|.NET-API|/System/Runtime/CompilerServices/_caller-information/logger.cs||

  }
  { main.cs

    gh|.NET-API|/System/Runtime/CompilerServices/_caller-information/main.cs||

  }
  { Another source file

    gh|.NET-API|/System/Runtime/CompilerServices/_caller-information/obj.cs||

  }
  { Compilation on the command line

    gh|.NET-API|/System/Runtime/CompilerServices/_caller-information/_compile.ps1||

  }


}
